   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##  Persisting High Scores with Local Storage\n",
    "Without local storage, scores vanish when you refresh the page. Local storage lets us keep the **high score**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example implementation:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "this.highScore = localStorage.getItem(\"highScore\") || 0;\n",
    "\n",
    "addScore(points) {\n",
    "    this.score += points;\n",
    "    if (this.score > this.highScore) {\n",
    "        this.highScore = this.score;\n",
    "        localStorage.setItem(\"highScore\", this.highScore);\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Teaching Explanation\n",
    "- `localStorage.setItem(key, value)` ‚Üí saves data to browser storage.\n",
    "- `localStorage.getItem(key)` ‚Üí retrieves saved data.\n",
    "- This persists across sessions (until the user clears it).\n",
    "\n",
    "üëâ This is an example of **data abstraction**: we don‚Äôt worry about how the browser stores data, we just use a simple API."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
